Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=PR101060|PR101060]){br}
You use this form to maintain deduction and benefit codes. A deduction code reduces the employee net pay and a benefit code increases the cost of payroll for the company. In Acumatica ERP, there is no actual difference between deduction and benefit codes for payroll calculation purposes—both may include an employee (deduction) and an employer (contribution) component, both may involve complex calculation methods, and both may or may not be subject to various taxes.{br}
By using this form, you can do the following: [anchor|#ul_d54_4ly_xv] *Define deduction and benefit codes, whether it is an employee deduction, an employer contribution or both. Code settings define how the system calculates benefits and deductions at a paycheck level. Upon release of the paycheck, the system creates liabilities for each code assigned to an employee. *Specify the vendor that is owed the liability. *Specify how this item affects taxes. *Specify the information related to the health insurance plan for ACA (Affordable Care Act) reporting purpose. *Specify if the code is keeping track of the workers’ compensation liabilities for a specific state. You need to create a benefit code for each state. The changes you make to rate and effective date on the '''WC Code''' tab will be propagated to the [HelpRoot_Payroll\PR_20_98_00|Work Class Compensation Codes] ([~/?ScreenId=PR209800|PR209800]) form after you save the changes. {br}{TOC} ==Form Toolbar==[anchor|#_29f4fa80-6992-42b4-8b80-076fce5fb1f0] The form toolbar includes only standard buttons. For the list of standard buttons, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Form_Toolbar|Form Toolbar]. ==Summary Area== You use the Summary area to specify the overall settings of the deduction or benefit.[anchor|#table_ytb_tly_xv] {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="20%" ! Element !width="80%" ! Description |- | '''Code''' | The unique identifier of the deduction or benefit. |- | '''Description''' | The description of the code to appear in such places as box selectors and pay stubs. |- | '''Contribution Type''' | The type of a code that defines how the code affects employee&rsquo;s earnings. The following options are available: [anchor|#_addaa903-ce8e-4978-b016-123796d7e15a] *''Employee Deduction'': The selected code is a deduction to the employee&rsquo;s earnings. With this option selected, the '''Employer Contribution Settings''' tab of this form becomes unavailable. *''Employer Contribution'': The selected code is a cont