Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=PR305000|PR305000]){br}
You can use this form to select a batch of direct deposit payments to employees; the batch can then be submitted for Automated Clearing House (ACH) processing.{br}
You can select a batch of payments for processing and then export the payments to a file by using the export scenario that is specified for the payment method on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CA_20_40_00|Payment Methods] ([~/?ScreenId=CA204000|CA204000]) form. The file with exported data can then be emailed to the appropriate bank or processed in another intended way.{br}
If an employee has multiple bank accounts configured, the form will display one line for each active bank account with the amount sent to this particular account.{br}{TOC} ==Form Toolbar==[anchor|#_5d2ff008-bf75-4a3a-a3b1-bd11800846cd] The form toolbar includes standard and form-specific buttons. For the list of standard buttons, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Form_Toolbar|Form Toolbar]. The form-specific buttons are listed below.[anchor|#table_ccx_g5s_xv] {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="20%" ! Button !width="80%" ! Description |- | '''Export''' | Exports the batch of payments to an ACH file, which is automatically attached to the batch record. |- | '''Release''' | Release the batch of payments and paychecks linked to the batch. |} ==Summary Area== By using the elements in this Summary area, you can select a batch of ACH payments and view its details.[anchor|#table_bxl_bvs_xv] {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="20%" ! Element !width="80%" ! Description |- | '''Reference Nbr.''' | The unique reference number of the batch of payments. |- | '''Status''' | The status of the batch, which the system assigns automatically. A batch can have one of the following statuses: ''On Hold'', ''Balanced'', ''Released'', or ''Exported''. |- | '''Hold''' | A check box that indicates (if selected) that the batch is on hold and cannot be exported. When you save a record with this check box selected, its status changes to ''On Hold''. This check box cannot be selected after the batch has been exported. |- | '''Batch Date''' | The date when the batch was created. |- | '''Cash Account''' | The cash account used for payment. |- | '''Payment Method''' | The payment method associated with the cash account. |- | '''File Export Time''' | The date and time when the export was performed. |- | '''Description''' | A description of the batch, which may help to identify it. |- | '''Batch Total''' | The total amount for the batch, which is calculated as the sum of all payment amounts. |} ==Table== This table contains the list of payment documents that make up the batch. The table may contain more than one row per payment number if the employee has chosen to split his paycheck between multiple bank accounts (for example, a checking account and a savings account). Also, if you decided to process multiple payments at the same time, multiple lines will get created.[anchor|#_b1cde167-0316-4461-81eb-b5627f58d8c9]{br}
