The user will always be able to add and remove PTO banks even if the '''Use PTO Banks from Employee Class''' check box is selected. The added bank will be active but will not use class default value since they are not part of the employee class. If a bank is not assigned in the employee class, the system clears the '''Use PTO Banks from Employee Class''' check box and makes it read-only. {br}
When an employee was using PTO bank from class and then cleared the '''Use PTO Banks from Employee Class''' check box, the system selects the '''Active''' check box and clears '''Use PTO Banks from Employee Class'''. {br}
If the employee decides to use PTO bank from class again, the banks from the class will be added with the '''Use PTO Banks from Employee Class''' and '''Active''' check boxes selected. If there are some classes already assigned to the employee, the system selects the '''Active''' check box and clears '''Use PTO Banks from Employee Class''' for the bank.{br}
When you remove a bank from the class while the employee has it active and using class default values and he or she is using PTO banks from class, the system clears both the '''Active''' and '''Use PTO Banks from Employee Class''' check boxes for the bank. When you remove a bank from the class while the employee has it active but not using class default and he or she is using PTO banks from class, the system selects the '''Active''' check box and clears '''Use PTO Banks from Employee Class''' for the bank. {br}
