Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=PR302000|PR302000]){br}
By using this form, you perform various operations related to pay checks. Ability to perform an operation depends on the payment type and its current status. Only one regular paycheck by pay period is allowed, but multiple specials and adjustments can be created.{br}
You can delete paychecks with the ''On Hold'', ''Needs Calculation'', and ''Pending Print/Payment'' statuses.{br}{TOC} ==Form Toolbar==[anchor|#_29d60132-6bbd-42fd-ad89-a95fe606e057] The form toolbar includes standard and form-specific buttons. For the list of standard buttons, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Form_Toolbar|Form Toolbar]. The form-specific buttons are listed below.[anchor|#table_ezr_g34_wv] ===Table Buttons=== {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="20%" ! Button !width="80%" ! Description |- | '''Actions''' | Provides the following menu commands, which you can click to invoke actions on one check at a time:[anchor|#ul_bxs_334_wv] *'''Calculate''': Performs all necessary calculations on the selected payment (taxes, PTO banks, benefits and deductions as well overtime for the paycheck). *'''Print Check''': Navigates to the [HelpRoot_Payroll\PR_50_50_00|Print Check] ([~/?ScreenId=PR505000|PR505000]) form to create a check or a direct deposit batch. *'''Cancel Print''': Cancels the '''Print Check''' action for the selected paycheck. The system changes paycheck status to ''Pending Print/Payment'' to allow you to correct errors. If the paycheck was part of a direct deposit batch, the system removes it from the batch as well. *:The action is available only for paychecks with the ''Printed/Paid'' status. *'''Release''': Posts summary amounts to payroll, creates GL transactions, and prints the GL posting journal. *'''Void''': Voids the payment by posting opposite transactions to the ledger and reversing the paycheck. *:This action is available only if the payment has been previously released.
|} ==Summary Area== You use the elements in this area to define a paycheck or an adjustment.[anchor|#table_mz3_lj4_wv] {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="20%" ! Element !width="80%" ! Description |- | '''Type''' | The payment type, which is one of the following options: [anchor|#_4669e2c4-29bf-495c-9a0d-e13921333620] *''Regular'': Represents a normal pay run for the paycheck. There will not be more than one by pay period. If you to create a paycheck for a pay period where there is already a paycheck, the system gives you the choice either to view the paycheck or continue editing (it will clear the pay period selection). *''Special'': Represents a not normal pay run for the paycheck. There could be as many as necessary by pay period. *''Adjustment'': Allows you to create a paycheck with negative and positive values outside of the normal life of the company. You can also adjust PTO using this type. The transactions created impact the GL as usual. You can edit any field in the paycheck and release it to update the value in the employee record. *''Void Check'': Appears when you click the '''Void''' action on the form toolbar.
|- | '''Reference Number''' | The unique identifier for this payment. |- | '''Status''' | The current status of the payment, which can be one of the following: [anchor|#_bd62d67b-cf84-4e2d-acaa-8b81b2f51cfb] *''Hold'': The document is a draft. It can be edited but cannot be released. This is the default status for new documents if the '''Hold on Entry''' check box is selected on [HelpRoot_Payroll\PR_10_10_00|Payroll Preferences]. *''Need Calculation'': The Hold check box is cleared for the document, but no paycheck has been generated. The document can be edited with this status. You click Calculate on the form toolbar to change the document status. *''Pending Print/Payment'': A paycheck has been calculated, but a check has not been printed or an ACH batch generated. *''Printed/Paid'': A check has been printed or an ACH batch has been generated and you can release the paycheck. You can edit only accounts and subaccounts. *''Released'': The paycheck is released. That is a payroll transaction is created and posted to general ledger. You cannot edit the document with this status. You can void documents with this status. *''Liability Partially Paid'': The liabilities created by the paycheck are partially processed to be converted to AP bills. You cannot void paychecks with this status. *''Closed'': all the liabilities linked with this paycheck have been processed to be converted to AP bills. You cannot void paychecks with this status. *''Voided'': The paycheck has been voided. Only documents with the ''Released'' status can be voided.
