Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=PR204000|PR204000]){br}
Many companies permit employees to accrue hours or days of PTO (paid time off) as they work, to use for sick or vacation leave. By using this form, you can define various PTO banks (accrual plans) for your employees.{br}
You can assign a PTO bank to an employee class that groups employees by certain type on the [HelpRoot_Payroll\PR_20_20_00|Employee Class] ([~/?ScreenId=PR202000|PR202000]) form or to an individual employee on the [HelpRoot_Payroll\PR_20_30_00|Employee Payroll Settings] ([~/?ScreenId=PR203000|PR203000]) form.{br}{TOC} ==Form Toolbar==[anchor|#_bc55b780-c218-40e3-8dc9-144a864b15f9] The form toolbar includes only standard buttons. For the list of standard buttons, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Form_Toolbar|Form Toolbar]. ==Summary Area== You can use the elements in this area to add a new PTO bank, or to view the details of an existing one. [anchor|#table_ypp_b4y_xv] {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="20%" ! Column !width="80%" ! Description |- | '''Bank ID''' | The unique identifier of a PTO bank to be used for the paid time off calculation. |- | '''Active''' | A check box that indicates (if selected) that the PTO bank should be accruing during the paycheck process. |- | '''Default Accrual Rate %''' | A default accrual rate to be used to accumulate hours each time a paycheck is released. |- | '''Accrue on Certified Job Only''' | A check box that indicates (if selected) that hours are accumulated only for the earning lines with the selected '''Certified''' check box in the released paycheck. |- | '''Accrual Limit (h)''' | The upper limit for the bank. Once the hours accumulated in the bank reach the limit, the system stops accruing the hours. |- | '''Start Date''' | The date at which the system starts accruing hours for an employee and adds the front loading number of hours to an employee PTO bank. You specify the number of hours in the '''Front Loading Amount''' box on the '''General Settings''' tab. |- | '''Disbursing Earning Type''' | An earning type code to be used to disburse it on a paycheck. When using the earning code on the paycheck it will reduce the bank by the number of hours entered on the line. The earning code can be used only once for a bank. |- | '''Description''' | The description of the PTO bank |} ==General Settings Tab== You use the settings on this tab to specify carry over and front loading rules.[anchor|#table_pqy_cty_xv] {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="20%" ! Column !width="80%" ! Description |- | '''Carryover Type''' | The way accruals are to be carried over from year to year starting the date specified in the '''Start Date''' box. The following options are available:[anchor|#_060bda82-57ba-424a-8e5a-ced7bc73f728] *''None'': The system starts over to accrue hours every year and resets unused hours. *''Partial'': The system carries over a number of hours accrued from the previous year. You specify how many hours to keep in the '''Carryover Amount''' box. *''Total'': The system carries over all accrued hours from the previous year.
|- | '''Carryover Amount''' | The number of hours the system carries over to the following year. |- | '''Front Loading Amount''' | The number of hours the system adds to the bank each year on a date specified in the '''Start Date''' box. |}

Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=PR103000|PR103000]){br}
Each payroll-related tax (whether it is of the employee withholding type or the employer type) is represented by a payroll tax code. The tax code describes the type of tax, the jurisdiction it is associated with, the tax agency that receives the tax payments, and the specific tax location information necessary for the calculation of the tax by the Symmetry Tax Engine software. Many taxes require additional detailed information, as mandated by the specific government entity, and these details are entered and maintained through attributes associated with the specific tax code.{br}
We recommend adding a tax code by using the '''Possible Taxes for this Location''' dialog box that you can open by clicking the '''View Tax List''' button available on the [HelpRoot_Payroll\PR_20_30_00|Employee Payroll Settings] ([~/?ScreenId=PR203000|PR203000]) and [HelpRoot_Payroll\PR_10_10_40|Work Locations] ([~/?ScreenId=PR101040|PR101040]) forms. By using this form, you can do the following: [anchor|#ul_p5s_p5y_xv] *Specify default settings for attributes associated with the tax and default GL accounts *Assign the vendor ID, for which a liability (and a subsequent Accounts Payable invoice) will be created for this tax {br}{TOC} ==Form Toolbar==[anchor|#_f1742f06-6543-43fe-8ac1-a3c25d38a45e] The form toolbar includes only standard buttons. For the list of standard buttons, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Form_Toolbar|Form Toolbar]. ==Summary Area==[anchor|#table_yzm_s5y_xv] {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="20%" ! Element !width="80%" ! Description |- | '''Code''' | The unique identifier of the tax. This code either represents a federal tax or is specific to a state or location. Thus, there would not be a tax code such as ''ST-WH'' (State Income Tax Withholding); something state-specific, such as ''AK-WH'' (Alaska State Income Tax Withholding), would be used instead. |- | '''Name''' | The description of the tax code. |- | '''Tax Category''' | The tax category, which determines whether the tax is on the employer (a liability only) or it is withheld from the employee’s paycheck (a deduction and a liability). The following options are available: ''Employer Contribution'' and ''Employee Withholding''. |- | '''Employer Govt. Tax ID''' | The specific government-issued identification code that the employer uses on tax returns and payments for this particular tax. Any previously entered employer government tax IDs on any other tax records are available so that you can copy the federal tax ID from one federal tax to another without having to retype it. |- | '''Vendor''' | The identifier of the entity to receive the tax liability payments for this tax. Only a vendor with the '''Vendor is Tax Agency''' check box selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_30_00|Vendors] ([~/?ScreenId=AP303000|AP303000]) form can be selected, although any valid vendor ID may be typed. |- | '''Invoice Descr. Source''' | The way the invoice description is generated, which also determines whether the '''Vendor Invoice Description''' box is available. The following options are available: [anchor|#ul_gry_x5y_xv] *''Code'' * ''Code Name'' * ''Payment Date'' * ''Payment Date + Code'' * ''Payment Date + Code Name'' * ''&lt;Free Format Entry&gt;'' (If this option is selected, the '''Vendor Invoice Description''' box is available.)
|- | '''Vendor Invoice Description''' | The description for the vendor invoice. This box is available only if the ''&lt;Free Format Entry&gt;'' option is selected in the '''Invoice Description Source''' box. |}[anchor|#table_zcs_cvy_xv] ===Tax Engine Info Section=== {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="20%" ! Element !width="80%" ! Description |- | '''Type''' | The specific type of tax with respect to the tax definitions in the Symmetry Tax Engine. The list of tax types available for selection is filtered based on the tax category selected above. |- | '''Jurisdiction Level''' | The jurisdiction level. When you select the tax type, the system displays one of the following options: ''Federal'', ''State'', ''Local'', ''Municipal'', or ''School District''. This setting determines whether the '''Tax Municipality Code''' and '''Tax School District Code''' boxes are available. |- | '''Wage Base Inclusion''' | The following options are available: ''State Specific'', ''Location Specific'', and ''All Wages''. This setting is validated to ensure that it is in sync with the jurisdiction level of the tax type; that is, you cannot select ''State Specific'' or ''Location Specific'' on a federal tax, and you cannot select ''Location Specific'' on a state tax. Local taxes and taxes at lower levels can use any setting. |- | '''Tax State''' | For federal jurisdiction taxes, the state is irrelevant, and for local jurisdiction taxes, a more specific location identifier in the form of the tax location code is required (see below). This box is available and required for all state jurisdiction taxes. |- | '''Get Tax Codes''' | A button that you click to automatically populate the '''Tax Unique ID''' box, which is a combination of the particular tax type and its location. |- | '''Tax Unique ID''' | A unique identifier that is generated when you click the '''Get Tax Codes''' button; this ID is a combination of the particular tax type and its tax location code. Every payroll tax in the United States is represented as a unique identifier in this box. The population of this box, which is required for the Symmetry Tax Engine to properly calculate the associated payroll tax, serves as validation that the Tax Engine recognizes the setup on this form as a valid tax. In some cases, the tax engine may return more than one possibility to choose from (for instance, where there are a number of identical tax types within a small geographic area); in this case, the selector is populated with the available options, and you must select and save one of the unique IDs from the list. |} ==Attributes Tab== This tab contains a list of the payroll attributes that are required for the specific tax being set up. This attribute list varies from state to state and from one tax to the next. For many typical taxes, the system automatically populates the required attributes. For others, especially for many types of local and municipal taxes, you need to determine the attributes that are required. See the Symmetry Tax Engine documentation for the attributes required for a specific local tax.[anchor|#_9d669b48-35f7-4147-b4c6-d91771df2aa6]{br}
